  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening of the Binational Dialogue between Haiti and the Dominican Republic to Promote Social Cohesion in the Border Area</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through a transnational approach, the proposed intervention aims to revitalize the Haiti - Dominican Republic Joint Bilateral Commission (CMB). This will be done in order to structure a binational governance model that includes and recognizes a plurality of actors and institutions at the local and national level that can contribute to the improvement of relations between the two countries, the creation of spaces for conflict resolution and the reduction of violence. This holistic approach is implemented to achieve the following results: (1) Border populations are aware of the positive contributions of safe, orderly and regular migration as well as of the benefits of peaceful binational relations; (2) Spaces for cross-border dialogue and local technical and cultural collaboration mechanisms are strengthened to promote social cohesion and the prevention of local conflicts in the border area; and (3) The CBM contributes to the strengthening of the binational dialogue between Haiti and the Dominican Republic, in particular in the field of security and migration.</narrative>
  </description>
